27 Section 2. Section 53-6-116, MCA, is amended to read:
28 "53-6-116. Medicaid managed care -- capitated health care. (1) The department of public health
- 5 - LC 451

****
69th Legislature 2025 LC 0451
1 and human services, in its discretion, may develop managed care and capitated health care systems for
2 medicaid recipients.
3 (2) The department may contract with one or more persons for the management of comprehensive
4 physical health services and the management of comprehensive mental health services for medicaid recipients.
5 The department may contract for the provision of these services by means of a fixed monetary or capitated
6 amount for each recipient.
7 (3) A managed care system is a program organized to serve the medical needs of medicaid
8 recipients in an efficient and cost-effective manner by managing the receipt of medical services for a
9 geographical or otherwise defined population of recipients through appropriate health care professionals.
10 (4) The provision of medicaid services through managed care and capitated health care systems is
11 not subject to the limitations provided in 53-6-104. The managed care or capitated health care system that is
12 provided to a defined population of recipients may be based on one or more of the medical assistance services
13 provided for in 53-6-101.
14 (5) The proposed systems, referred to in subsection (1), must be submitted to the legislative
15 finance committee. The legislative finance committee shall review the proposed systems at its next regularly
16 scheduled meeting and shall provide any comments concerning the proposed systems to the department. The
17 department shall provide a copy of any reports made to the legislative finance committee concerning the
18 proposed systems to the legislature in accordance with 5-11-210.
19 (6) A managed care or capitated health care system, except for a primary care case management
20 service, that requires for implementation a waiver from the centers for medicare and medicaid is subject to the
21 provisions of Title 53, chapter 6, part 7.
22 (7) The department may not require an enrollee to participate in a primary care case management
23 service if the enrollee enters into a direct primary care contract."
